Sinclair Broadcast Group, Inc. (SBGI) Shares Bought by Kissinger Financial Services LLC

Eneas Benito |
Lunes, Julio 24, 2017







Sinclair Broadcast Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:SBGI) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
Sinclair Broadcast Group earned a media sentiment score of 0.36 on Accern's scale. (NASDAQ:SBGI) by 75.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Independent Portfolio Consultants Inc. now owns 2,575 shares of the company's stock worth $104,000 after buying an additional 60 shares in the last quarter. Kissinger Financial Services LLC's holdings in Sinclair Broadcast Group were worth $287,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 1,371,571 shares of the company's stock worth $55,549,000 after buying an additional 1,342,400 shares during the period. Wells Fargo & Company MN now owns 120,546 shares of the company's stock valued at $4,883,000 after buying an additional 3,995 shares during the last quarter. Equities analysts expect that Sinclair Broadcast Group will post $2.04 EPS for the current year. One investment analyst has rated the stock with a hold rating and seven have issued a buy rating to the company. M&T Bank Corp purchased a new stake in shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group during the first quarter valued at approximately $213,000. Finally, Kingdon Capital Management L.L.C. raised its position in shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group by 475.5% in the first quarter. (NASDAQ:SBGI) stock soared 1.35% to $33.75 on the closing of 07/19/2017.(NASDAQ:SBGI) shares saw light trading volume with 519K shares changing hands on Wednesday. In terms of relative volume, these shares are trading at 1.02x their normal volume. The firm's 50 day moving average price is $33.69 and its 200-day moving average price is $36.10. The stock appeared $43.05 above its 52-week highs and is up 4.23% for the last five trades. SBGI's current price-earnings ratio amounts to 11.15 times earnings, below the average P/E ratio of 21.08 times earnings.
Press coverage about Sinclair Broadcast Group (NASDAQ:SBGI) has been trending positive recently, Accern reports. Excluding an unfavorable currency impact, at prevailing exchange rates, of around $0.14 for the full-year 2017, as well as the favorable tax item of $0.04 recorded in the first quarter of 2017, the forecast range represents a projected increase of around 9% to 12% versus adjusted earnings per share in 2016. As the returns are concern, return on equity was recorded 39.70% and firm surged its return on investment 9.30% while its return on asset stayed at 4.70%. The business had revenue of $649.90 million during the quarter, compared to analysts' expectations of $646.94 million. State Street Corp raised its stake in Sinclair Broadcast Group by 0.6% in the fourth quarter. Stephens set a $46.00 target price on shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group and gave the stock a "buy" rating in a report on Saturday, June 3rd.ILLEGAL ACTIVITY NOTICE: This piece was posted by The Cerbat Gem and is owned by of The Cerbat Gem. If you are accessing this story on another website, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of United States and worldwide trademark and copyright law. The original version of this piece can be accessed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/23/rbf-capital-llc-holds-stake-in-sinclair-broadcast-group-inc-sbgi-updated-updated-updated.html. Denver Investment Advsrs Limited Liability Company stated it has 1.05% in Sinclair Broadcast Group Inc (NASDAQ:SBGI). It turned negative, as 29 investors sold Sinclair Broadcast Group Inc shares while 70 reduced holdings. Finally, Benchmark Co. increased their price target on Sinclair Broadcast Group from $45.00 to $52.00 and gave the company a "buy" rating in a report on Thursday, May 4th. ValuEngine upgraded shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group from a "hold" rating to a "buy" rating in a research report on Tuesday, May 16th. Royal Bank Of Canada restated a "buy" rating and set a $45.00 target price on shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group in a research report on Wednesday, July 5th. Sinclair Broadcast Group now has a consensus rating of "Buy" and a consensus price target of $44.40.In other news, Director Lawrence E. Mccanna sold 2,000 shares of the company's stock in a transaction that occurred on Wednesday, June 14th. The stock was sold at an average price of $34.75, for a total value of $69,500.00. Also, insider David D. Smith bought 4,400 shares of Sinclair Broadcast Group stock in a transaction dated Friday, May 5th. The shares were bought at an average price of $36.77 per share, for a total transaction of $161,788.00. The disclosure for this purchase can be found here.Sinclair Broadcast Group, Inc is a television broadcasting company. The Company also owns digital and Internet media products that are complementary to its portfolio of television station related digital properties.




