            Team Assemblers
            
        






Production Assembler

at Sinclair Broadcast Group


Date Posted: 
7/25/2017




Apply




Not ready to Apply?








                        Job Description
                    


Based in Raymond, Maine, Dielectric LLC is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Sinclair Broadcast Group, Inc. and is a leading provider of innovative broadcast products. From remote stations to major markets, Dielectric delivers products for every need since 1942 and prides itself on being a solution-oriented engineering company. The Company is a trusted partner of broadcasters worldwide. We design, engineer, and manufacture antennas, combiners, switches, diplexers, transmission lines and waveguides for television, and FM radio. We collaborate with the consultant community, as well as with its customers' engineering staffs, to design advanced and reliable antenna systems.We are currently seeking full-time Production Assemblers. We are looking for someone who can help us construct and assemble component parts, building of transmission lines, soldering, and assist in the shipping and receiving of internal and external products. The ideal candidate will be familiar with standard concepts, practices, and procedures within a particular field. In this position, you will perform a variety of tasks and works under general supervision.Duties and Responsibilities:Works with production specifications and plant data for product assemblyAble to produce a quality product in a safe and timely mannerBe aware of defects before product completionAble to multi-taskPrepares products for shipping and receiving as directedOther duties as assignedRequired Skills:Excellent Organizational skillsAble to work across functions and in team oriented environmentGood communication skillsDetail oriented; analytical with strong problem solving abilitiesAble to follow all safety rules and regulationsMust be willing to be trained in all areas of productionMachining experience a plusWillingness to learn the painting process a plusAble to use basic hand and power toolsReview and interpret manufacturer’s designs in EnglishPhysical Requirements:Must be able to lift up to 50 lbs. oftenMust be able to operate all equipment safely and within the manufacturers specificationsThe employee is required to stand, walk, reach with arms and hands, climb or balance, and to stoop, kneel and crouch frequentlyDielectric is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and a drug free workplace!






Apply




Not ready to Apply?










Share With







